The Roadmap contains plans for future releases of OpenTTD. For information on previous releases, see the [[en/Archive/OpenTTD/Main Page|release history]].

==0.5.0 ==
*electrified railways
*subsidiaries (formerly feeder system)
*path based signalling
*signal autocompletion
*clone vehicles
*realistic catchment area
*station statistics
*automatic presignals
*string extension: using {:X} ({STRING:2}{COMMA16:1})
*keep working on the console wherever needed
*new pathfinding
''(See also: [[en/Archive/Lists/Roadmap 0.5]])''

==0.6.0==
*new map array
*new tile file format (CGD)
*24-Bit graphics
*AlphaBlending blitter for 32-bit CGD
*maybe a new audio format
*full flexible track/road layout under bridges
*signals on bridges/tunnels
*different signals on different tracks in same tile
*crossing bridges
*cargo destinations
*passenger destinations
*balancing of values (i.e. transporting fare)
''(See also: [[en/Archive/Lists/Roadmap 0.6]])''

==0.7.0==
*unicode fonts
*new string system
*complete new open graphics
*balancing of values (costs, production rates, etc.)
*use gettext (http://www.gnu.org/software/gettext/) for i18n support
*full Intergration with graphics website
''(See also: [[en/Archive/Lists/Roadmap 0.7]])''